  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.7\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\nThe following code compiles but generates incorrect code\r\n```vyper\r\n@external\r\ndef foo():\r\n    raw_call(msg.sender, convert(b\"\", bytes32))\r\n```\r\nthe relevant IR:\r\n```\r\n[seq,\r\n  [mstore,\r\n    96,\r\n    /* convert(b\"\", bytes32) */ \r\n    [with,\r\n      arg,\r\n      /* b\"\" */ [seq, [mstore, 64, 0], 64],\r\n      [with,\r\n        bits,\r\n        [shl, 3, [sub, 32, [mload, arg]]],\r\n        [shl, bits, [shr, bits, [mload, [add, arg, 32]]]]]]],\r\n  96],\r\n[call, gas, caller <msg.sender>, 0 <value>, 128, [mload, 96], 0, 0]]],\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nWe should block the behavior, or implement correct codegen for it",
